Your publish is still going through the **Web Publishing Pipeline package flow**, not a plain folder publish.

The giveaway is in your log:

```text
PreTransformWebConfig
PipelineMsdeploySpecificTransformPhase
CopyAllFilesToSingleFolderForMsdeploy
```

That means MSBuild is still building a **web deploy/package-style staging output**, which is why you see content under `obj\Any CPU\Release\Package\PackageTmp` and why your `packageLocation` folder does not exist for the zip step.

## Why this happens

In classic .NET Framework web projects, these flags are not enough by themselves:

```yaml
/p:DeployOnBuild=true
/p:WebPublishMethod=FileSystem
```

Because without the right publish target/output properties, the old web publishing pipeline can still stage files under `obj\...\Package\PackageTmp`.

Also, your zip task is trying to archive:

```text
$(Build.ArtifactStagingDirectory)\AlternaCardManagement-package-mvc
```

but your publish step never wrote there, so `ArchiveFiles@2` fails.

---

# What to change

Replace your publish step with this exact version:

```yaml
- task: VSBuild@1
  displayName: 'Publish to folder'
  condition: and(succeeded(), ne('${{ parameters.buildProject }}', ''))
  inputs:
    solution: '${{ parameters.buildProject }}'
    vsVersion: '${{ parameters.vsVersion }}'
    platform: '${{ parameters.buildPlatform }}'
    configuration: '${{ parameters.buildConfiguration }}'
    clean: false
    msbuildArgs: >
      /p:SkipInvalidConfigurations=true
      /p:VisualStudioVersion=${{ parameters.vsVersion }}
      /p:DeployOnBuild=true
      /p:DeployDefaultTarget=WebPublish
      /p:WebPublishMethod=FileSystem
      /p:PublishUrl="${{ parameters.packageLocation }}"
      /p:DeleteExistingFiles=true
      /p:AutoParameterizationWebConfigConnectionStrings=false
```

## Important changes

Use these:

```yaml
/p:DeployDefaultTarget=WebPublish
/p:PublishUrl="..."
```

Do **not** use these for your scenario:

```yaml
/p:PackageLocation="..."
/p:PackageAsSingleFile=false
```

Those are for package/webdeploy style output, not for “publish flat folder then zip it”.

---

# Why the zip step failed

Because this folder was expected:

```text
C:\agent\_work\6\a\AlternaCardManagement-package-mvc
```

but the publish never created it.

After the fix above, the publish should actually write there, and then this zip step will work:

```yaml
- task: ArchiveFiles@2
  displayName: 'Zip publish output'
  inputs:
    rootFolderOrFile: '${{ parameters.packageLocation }}'
    includeRootFolder: false
    archiveType: 'zip'
    archiveFile: '$(Build.ArtifactStagingDirectory)\${{ parameters.zipName }}'
    replaceExistingArchive: true
```

